Interface FormFieldStyler

  • All Superinterfaces:

    • Method Detail

      • create

        com.itextpdf.text.pdf.BaseField create()
                                       throws com.vectorprint.VectorPrintException
        Creates the correct BaseField based on the FormFieldStyler.FIELDTYPE of this styler. The FormFieldStyler in the chain of stylers that created the BaseField should be registered as a cell event to the PdfPCell being styled. Subsequent stylers can call getFromCell(java.lang.Object) to get hold of the BaseField and apply their styling to it. When the cell event fires makeField() can be used to create the actual form field.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        com.vectorprint.VectorPrintException
